From 6a6833858d4e107b49daddcfc9a4f2dd77609340 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kannan Saravanan <kannsara@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2025 15:44:44 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi:ath12k: Add Mode2 recovery support for
 MLO
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

In the Mode 2 recovery design, the system is configured to support
the MLD station during SSR recovery of the affected radio.

+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+
| Recovery    | Behavior                                                     |
| Mode        |                                                              |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+
| Mode 1      | - Recover only the affected radio.                           |
|             | - Active radio will serve only the legacy stations.          |
|             | - MLD stations will be disconnected during recovery.         |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+
| Mode 2      | - Recover only the affected radio.                           |
|             | - Active radio will serve both legacy and MLD stations.      |
|             | - Crashed radio will send disassoc to MLD stations during    |
|             |   recovery.                                                  |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+

The firmware is checked to determine whether it supports MLO peer
recovery using the service bitmap. Based on this capability,
SSR is toggled between Mode 1 and Mode 2.

If Mode 2 is enabled on the host, all MLO peers and legacy peers from
partner SoCs—are retained during the recovery of the asserted SoC.
The current design ensures that MLD peer cleanup on partner SoCs is prevented.

This follows same mode1 existing implementation, so the hardware queue is
restarted, traffic flow resumes for SoCs that were not affected after umac
reset. After recovery, key addition on partner SoCs is blocked,
since cleanup was not performed for those unaffected SoCs.
Disassociation messages are sent only for the MLD peers that were
connected to the crashed radio.

Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <gauthamk@qti.qualcomm.com>
